Follow the commands and then run the .py file.

1) pip list > piplist.txt
2) open piplist.txt and delete the following lines: 

{
Package                     Version
--------------------------- --------------------
}


( you only want the:  "(installation) == (version)" inside the piplist.txt file)

3) run the .py file. This will create the piplist_new.txt.
4) copy the content of the piplist_new.txt. and paste it inside the terminal or the virtual environment.
5) Wait for the installation.
